metadata.name: Sky Imagination #91
metadata.description:
It is an interactive piece created with p5.js that allows the viewer to imagine different things as they watch the clouds and colors of the sky converge and change. 
The artwork aims to evoke the feeling of wonder and curiosity, 
inviting the viewer to explore their imagination and discover new possibilities.

metadata.name: Plottable Era: (I) Primitive #365
metadata.description:
'Plottable Era: (I) Primitive' is the first generator in the "Era" generators series, highlighting different periods and civilizations. This first series "Primitive" shows the beginning of mankind with people exploring the mountains and traveling on the sea during sunset.

The digital version simulates ink effects and adds a subtle animation over the water. Each outcome is also physically plottable with pens: A SVG file can be exported (right-click save) to plot the piece physically. The plots are designed to be executed in A4 format on either fountain pens (on white paper) or gel pens (Black / Blue).

Thanks to the utility token decoupling, you can get a physical version: the digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece, owning it confers the right to plot or request a physical plot from @greweb (https://greweb.me/plots/nft). @greweb would use fountain pens but other plotting artists are free to achieve it with their own materials and ship to collectors – as long as NFT is owned at request time.

More details and Source code: https://github.com/gre/gre/tree/master/doodles/plottable-era-primitive

@greweb – 2022 – tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM – CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

reserve is set to previous 2022 physical plot collectors.

metadata.name: Sierras #37
metadata.description:
This is meant to look like a hand drawn map you might find in a fantasy book. It's also inspired by the landscapes I've seen along the California coast and the Sierra Nevada mountains.

In live mode, once the art is generated, tap the 's' key to save a large version of it.

Enjoy!

metadata.name: Foundations #227
metadata.description:
In march of this year, I started working on a new series involving multi-layering, and overriding shapes. Drawing and playing with colors and opacity.
It started with squares and grid, it then involved deformations, and circles and other experimentations.
This path fits with my artistic generative approach: rather than having a completely predefined idea, I start with a simple concept that evolves during creation. Then surprises happened, and I embraced them.

But this year was not like any other: 2022 has gifted me with a new birthday, the one of my son.

Over the past twelve months, I’ve watched him discovering the world surrounding him, learning and trying new things, laughing, or getting frustrated, sad or happy…
While learning to become a parent, I’ve been in an introspection phase where I questioned what it means to be “a father”. What impact will I have on my son, consciously or not?

“Foundations” takes shape in this context: 2 humans trying and exploring while being inspired by each other.
This series is a first of a set of at least 3, that illustrates an idea of what is an “Identity”, and what makes us who we are.

The foundations of an identity are laid in the first days of a child’s life. They will be influenced by many factors; including parenting, cultural environment, life experiences… 
Of course, as humans we are in constant evolution; life happens, sometimes for the best, sometimes for the worst, and our personality will be impacted…
But this will be a topic for another time. 


Today, we are at the start.

metadata.name: Ridge Blur #339
metadata.description:
This work is the second in the ridge series. While using the same base algorithm this work is about exploring landscapes using a much more dark and desolate imagery.

It was designed to be experienced in fullscreen in live mode.
Press "s" to save a screenshot.

Dutch auction (14/11/8), updating every 5min.

Original artwork by William Watkins · Lyon, 2022

metadata.name: sauce #51
metadata.description:
sauce is the sister project of "sphaghetti al dente". both have been explorations into noise, and also a look into the amount of visual complexity that can be achieved via simple math and simple shapes layered on each other...

sauce is only available for the holders of "spaghetti al dente", and the reason I go out of my way to make it a free mint as usual is that this project will give 99% of both the primary and the secondary proceeds to IRAN. let's help as much as any of us can...

I have imported the wallet list of holders of spaghetti but removed the address-only wallets , my apologies if your wallet got chopped, but anyway the edition number is already way way lower than spaghetti.

Sauce also completes my self-imposed task/burden of publishing 12 projects in my first year in genart. I have started exactly on 3rd of january last year to learn and thanks to all of your generosity and interest in my work, I was able to finish my mission. 

peace.

metadata.name: A Distant Memory #179
metadata.description:
A distant memory of trees, buildings and the old village. Once a moment, the memory is illuminated by a beam of light, which gives me the insight of this work.

--------------------

This is an abstract generation made by pure code.

--------------------

In live mode, press 's' or 'S' to save a high resolution png.

Please be patient with drawing process (it'll take one minute in my computer).
This is my last artwork in 2022. I hope you like this work.

Endlessworld 2022
